# SourceView Landing Site Rules

## Project Overview
SourceView landing site built with Next.js App Router, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS.
Google Fonts: Playfair Display (serif headings), Outfit (body), JetBrains Mono (mono accents).
Color system uses CSS custom properties (--god, --lead, --support, --narrator, --ruby, --ink, --bg).

## TypeScript Rules
- ALWAYS use TypeScript — no JavaScript files
- Strict mode enabled — no implicit any
- Type everything explicitly — interfaces for all data structures
- No type assertions unless absolutely necessary

## React Component Rules
- ONLY functional components — no class components
- Use modern hooks — useState, useEffect, useMemo, useCallback, useContext
- Server Components first — use Client Components ("use client") only when needed (animations, event handlers, intersection observers)
- Define explicit interfaces for all component props
- Component file structure:
  ```typescript
  import { FC } from 'react';

  interface ComponentNameProps {
    // ...
  }

  export const ComponentName: FC<ComponentNameProps> = ({ prop1, prop2 }) => {
    return (/* JSX */);
  };
  ```

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `SphereView`, `ProductCard`)
- Files: kebab-case for pages (e.g., `sourceview-bible/page.tsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase with 'use' prefix (e.g., `useRevealOnScroll`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., `PRODUCT_ITEMS`)
- Utilities: camelCase (e.g., `formatDate`)

## Tailwind & Styling
- Mobile-first: always start with mobile styles, add breakpoints up (sm, md, lg, xl)
- Spacing scale: use Tailwind's default (4px base unit)
- Prefer CSS animations/transitions over JavaScript animation libraries
- Use CSS custom properties for the SourceView color system alongside Tailwind utilities

## Performance
- First Contentful Paint: < 1.5s
- Time to Interactive: < 3.5s
- Use Next.js Image component for all images
- Lazy load components below the fold
- Prefetch critical navigation paths (product pages)

## Semantic HTML & Accessibility
- Use proper semantic elements: section, nav, main, footer, article
- All images must have descriptive alt text
- Interactive elements need aria labels where context is not obvious
- Color contrast must meet WCAG AA
- All external links must use target="_blank" with rel="noopener noreferrer"

## Testing Checklist
Before considering any feature complete:
- [ ] Test on mobile viewport (320px width)
- [ ] Test on tablet viewport (768px width)
- [ ] Test on desktop viewport (1920px width)
- [ ] Test with slow network (Chrome DevTools throttling)

## Planning Process (Required)
1. Explain your approach in 2-3 sentences
2. Identify dependencies — what needs to exist first?
3. Consider edge cases — what could go wrong?
